constructor.t.sol
├─ when the auction contract is set to the zero address
│  └─ it should revert
└─ when the auction contract is not set to the zero address
   ├─ when the auction contract does not support the IBaseAuction interface
   │  └─ it should revert
   └─ when the auction contract supports the IBaseAuction interface
      ├─ when the auction contract does not support the IPriceManager interface
      │  └─ it should revert
      └─ when the auction contract supports the IPriceManager interface
         ├─ when the auction bidder is set to the zero address
         │  └─ it should revert
         └─ when the auction bidder is not set to the zero address
            ├─ when the auction bidder does not support the IAuctionBidder interface
            ├─ it should revert
            └─ when the auction bidder supports the IAuctionBidder interface
               ├─ when there are workflow ids to be configured
               │  ├─ when the workflow id is set to zero
               │  │  └─ it should revert
               │  └─ when the workflow id is not set to zero
               │     ├─ it should set the workflow ids
               │     └─ it should emit a WorkflowIdSet event
               ├─ it should set the auction contract
               ├─ it should emit an AuctionSet event
               ├─ it should support the correct interfaces
               └─ it should return the correct type and version
